list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: the fleshy muscular organ in the mouth of a mammal, used for tasting, licking, swallowing, and (in humans) articulating speech.
used in reference to a person's style or manner of speaking.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: he was a redoubtable debater with a caustic tongue

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: a strip of leather or fabric under the laces in a shoe, attached only at the front end.
the free-swinging metal piece inside a bell which is made to strike the bell to produce the sound.
a long, low promontory of land.
a projecting strip on a wooden board fitting into a groove on another.
the vibrating reed of a musical instrument or organ pipe.
